Job Proposal: Battery Dispatch Optimization with GAMSpy Project Objective We want to refine a battery optimization model for electricity market participation. The repository already contains a working prototype that reads price and demand series from Excel, formulates a linear program with GAMSpy, and stores results in a SQLite database. However, recent test runs do not yield plausible schedules for charging, discharging, and self-consumption. We seek an expert to review and optimize the GAMSpy model. Scope of Work Model Review and Debugging Inspect the existing GAMSpy code in model.py and related modules to ensure constraints and objective function correctly reflect the intended battery operations. Verify that key aspects such as mutual exclusivity of charging/discharging and fixed end-of-horizon state of charge are properly enforced. Data Processing Workflow Confirm that the Excel input is loaded correctly through data_loader.py. Ensure chunk-based processing in processor.py and scenario.py is consistent with the solver’s requirements. Optimization Enhancements Suggest improvements to solver settings (e.g., CPLEX options) or GAMSpy formulations that might improve convergence and solution quality. Investigate and resolve any issues that cause the model to produce unrealistic dispatch schedules. Results Validation Validate the output metrics stored in results.sqlite, including full cycles, energy turnover, and weighted prices, as documented in the schem Cross-check KPIs with the Excel/CSV results to confirm internal consistency. Expected Outcome An updated GAMSpy model that reliably generates plausible charging and discharging schedules for predefined scenarios (epex, intraday, both). Clear instructions in the README or supplemental documentation describing any configuration or parameter changes required for reproducible results. Optional: recommendations on how to further extend the model (e.g., efficiency losses, degradation) or integrate with the existing Flask/Next.js dashboards. Qualifications Proven experience with GAMS/GAMSpy and linear programming. Familiarity with electricity market modeling and battery storage economics. Strong Python skills for working within the current codebase. Ability to analyze solver logs and fine-tune optimization parameters.
